<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=198188"> My Profile</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uteaenea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teaenea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/21/02 7:12:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ketel Kaotic</span><hr size=1> A few things to consider.<br>
<br>
People keep talking about a guild being KS'd by a roaming band of wizards.  Can it happen.  I guess, but, if a guild already has a dragon engaged and this happens, the PnP was just violated.  Something can be done.  This is why you won't see KS'ng happen very often.<br>
<br>
Mobs being insta-killed.  I'm not concerned here either.  The highly contested mobs are already insta-killed.  Sev is usually dead within minutes of popping.  On CT, there are tons of potiential manaburn victims that are not insta-killed.  Gore, Talendor, Venril, Trak are often up for hours or days.<br>
<br>
On CT, NToV has a rotation going.  You won't see any KS'ng there unless they want big trouble.  All other Dragons are a FFA.  <br>
<br>
There are very few mobs where a band of Wizards can kill an old uber (Gore, Talendor, Sev, are no longer really considered uber) as they need to get to the mob.  You won't see 6 wizards going in to Sebilis to Kill Trak.  You need a bit more than that to get there.  Venril is a bit easier, but, you still need to get there.  Then again, None of these Mobs need huge forces to kill them anymore.  I've witnessed a single group kill Sev.  No, not wizards, though, one wiz was a part of the group.  It was a Rogue, Warrior, SK, Cleric, Shaman, Wizard.  They were equipted well.  They were a group of friends from various uberguilds.<br>
<br>
Getting 10 of any class together for one kill is a feat, never mind Wizards.  Ok, you can get about 1000 druids for UP or Fear. =P  Wizards are not the most common class.  Manaburners, for the moment, are only a small segment of that group.  I belong to a fairly large guild.  150+members.  (alone, we have about 4 manaburners) We can take out all old ubers in house.  We can do as much as Vindi.  We have an alliance with a similar guild.  We do slightly bigger mobs with them.  Even with our two guilds fielding people, we never have 10 wizards.  Heck, we never have 10 clerics, warriors, or any class for that matter.  The idea that soon you'll see 25mana burning Wizards taking out mobs with 200K hp, is far fetched at best.  If this has a chance to happen, why did we never see 20+ icecomet casting wizards taking out Naggy all the time?<br>
<br>
Gratz to all the wizards on this accomplishment.  Considering, this ability is still very situational, at best, it's pretty cool. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uteaenea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teaenea</A> at: 6/21/02 7:15:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearsthe2nd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfears The2nd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/21/02 7:35:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No crying over spilled milk..just please, think for a sec..</span><hr size=1> Ok. What is done is done.  I think it is awesome from a RP perspective what has been done, and no, by no means is this an easy feat to replicate.  I am a wizard.  I understand this.  Here is the problem:<br>
<br>
Most people that are clamouring about this feat being unbalanced and overpowered are not going to be Wizards.  They are not going to understand how difficult this is.  They, if anything, are going to be envious melee's that are accustomed to being on top of the food chain.  Has Verant ever been known to cater to Melee's whims before ?  We both know the answer to this.<br>
<br>
Secondly, how have nerfs happened in the past ?  How does Verant recognize it's oversight on balance and readress these things that have been aforementioned in previous posts.  Think real hard about this..how ?   By random Verant employee playing the same game ?  NO.  By a sinlge person complaining..&quot;Hey, this sucks !!&quot;..NO.<br>
<br>
The real reason ?  100's if not 1000's of emails sent to the Devs corner or /feedbacks, thusly prompting Alan to begin his posts &quot;After evaluating the considerable feedback, we have decided to reconsider...&quot;  Sound familiar ?  Well it should.<br>
<br>
Thirdly, what do you think is the quickest way to ensure that the RATE at which these &quot;/feedback manaburn is overpowered, this is proof&quot; or emails come pouring in ?  Do you think this would happen faster if we post on all the Warrior, necro, bard, mage, rogue boards that we have just taken down a high end Raid mob with this skill that they are already up in arms about ?  I hope you make the connection here.  This is common sense.<br>
<br>
The greasy wheel gets the grease first.  A few people clamouring to ge this nerfed will do nothing.  1/2 of Verants customer base sure the heck will.  And this, my friends, is the quickest way to ensure this happens sooner then later..and exactly the reason as to why it should cease immediately.  This is not paranio, this is being smart.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ney<br>
